Dairy Farmers Corner Hunter & Tighe Street

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE & Commercial Collective are pleased to present the Dairy Farmers Corner to market for sale by Expressions of Interest.

Dairy Farmers Corner offers a substantial development opportunity which will suit commercial, residential, retail and hotel use (STCA). The site is positioned on the 'West End' and is identified by council as the new CBD, surrounded by an array of large format retailers, bustling cafes and a walk to the Transport Interchange. 

Key attributes:

• Iconic Newcastle corner location, Newcastle’s Famous “Dairy Farmers Corner”
• Three street frontages – Hunter Street, Railway Street and Tighe Street
• Expansive 5,130sqm site area – 10 separate allotments
• 90m height limit – the maximum allowable in Newcastle CBD
• Maximum 8:1 FSR (commercial) and 5:1 (residential)
• Not affected by mine subsidence – eliminated significant cost and construction risk 
• Significant holding income – fixed leases in place with demo clauses
• Strong supporting demographics within the local and broader catchment 
• Newcastle: Australia's largest regional economy with population of 450,000 and growing

EOI closing Thursday, 19 November 2020 at 4PM.
For more information, please contact the exclusive sales agents.

*approximate

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: PROMINENT CBD DEVELOPMENT SITE WITH HOLDING INCOME

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: One of Newcastle’s most coveted hotels
Sale includes Hotel Licence and 22 PME's

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Hotels, along with Moore and Moore Real Estate are delighted to be appointed to sell the freehold going concern interest in Hotel Delany.

Key investment considerations include:
  
– Widely considered one of Newcastle’s most coveted hotels
– Situated at the heart of Newcastle’s ‘Eat Street’ Precinct amongst a thriving retail, dining, fashion and art scene – comparable to Sydney’s Crown Street, Surry Hills
– Premium 1,684sqm* retail footprint on the ever popular Darby Street
– Proximate to Newcastle’s $750m landmark ‘East End’ Project (13 minute walk) set to transform the Newcastle City Centre and attract more than 5,000 new residents, mixed businesses and retail tenants across four separate stages
– Council carpark at the rear of the hotel offering convenience and security for patrons
– Favourable planning controls including B4 Mixed Use zoning, 2:1 FSR, 14m Height Limit
– Hotel offers substantial opportunity to reconfigure and reposition in light of Newcastle's resurgence and significant recent government investment
– Sale includes Hotel Licence with 22 Poker Machine Entitlements – OLGR approved to 2am^

^DA approval pending
*approximate

Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Located at the heart of Newcastle CBD

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE, Commercial Collective and Moore & Moore Real Estate are pleased to present the Civic Portfolio to market.

Comprising three iconic buildings at the heart of Newcastle’s business and cultural district, the properties offer secure commercial investments with a rich history, ideally located just metres from the city’s waterfront. Offered in-one-line or individually, the buildings provide significant value-add potential through refurbishments and conversion, whilst the large amalgamated site allows the opportunity to capitalise on its strong development upside in the future (S.T.C.A).

The Civic Portfolio benefits from the following key attributes:

- Clarendon Hotel, Fred Ash Building & Bennett Building offered in-one-line or individually
- Diversified tenant mix: hotel, office and retail
- Combined site area of 2,336sqm* with development upside (S.T.C.A)
- Zoned B3 Commercial Core with 4:1 FSR and 30 metre height limit
- Total floor area of 3,416sqm*
- Excellent income with further refurbishment & conversion potential
- Ideally located at the heart of Newcastle CBD's business and cultural district in a high profile corner location
- Moments from the waterfront and the Newcastle Light Rail network
- Fred Ash Building NABERS Energy rating: 5-Stars

Tenders have now closed for this property. 

For more information, please contact the exclusive sales agents.


Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Prospective purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

*approximate
*outlines indicative only
